The compensation of the fund manager is called a'management fee' and is paid by the fund for the services provided (advice, analyses, fund management and reporting). This fee is generally 1.25%11 to 2.5%12 per year for a direct investment fund (around 0.5-1% per year for a fund of funds), depending on the fund size. This fee is calculated on the fund size13 during the investment period, and usually on the NAV of the portfolio once the investment period has ended.

