**Lifespan of a fund**: For a closed-end (_see this expression_) fund, the start of the lifespan of a private market fund is determined by either its first or its last closing, depending on the fund regulations. The end is usually determined by the fund regulations as well, including extensions. At times, the lifespan of a closed-end private market fund can extend beyond what was planned by the fund regulations. For an evergreen (_see this expression_) fund, the lifespan starts at the creation of the structure and is indefinite.
