**Monitoring fees**: To monitor and control a portfolio company, LBO fund managers can decide to charge to the company an annual fee. This fee can be attributed to the fund manager, the fund investors or shared between the fund manager and the fund investors.
**Most favoured nation clause**: Provision of a fund regulation in which the fund managers agree to automatically provide each fund investor with the best terms negotiated by any other investor in the fund, including by way of direct negotiation with the fund manager in a side letter (_see this expression_), for example.
